article.headline: Jones, Lyttle supply all Houston's second-half points
article.linkText: Houston's Jones, Lyttle upset No. 17 TCU
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Chandi Jones banked in a jump shot with
29 seconds left, leading Houston to a 61-59 win over TCU (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) on
Sunday.

Jones finished with a game-high 32 points. She and Sancho
Lyttle, who finished with 12 points, supplied all the second-half
scoring for Houston (14-2, 3-0 C-USA).

Amy Pack scored 13 points for TCU (13-3, 2-1). Sandora Irvin
added 11 points and 12 rebounds.

TCU had a chance to tie the game in the final seconds, but Pack
missed a free throw and Jones grabbed her eighth rebound with 2
seconds left.

Jones was fouled and made one of two free throws to complete the
scoring.
